title: Bug 6322 - All Types Dialog Shows Obfuscated Classes
description: The bug report highlights that the 'All Types' dialog displays obfuscated classes from JDK 1.4, including 'a,' 'a1,' 'b,' 'c,' 'd,' etc.
OB: The observed behavior is not explicitly stated in the report. However, it can be inferred that obfuscated classes are displayed prominently in the 'All Types' dialog.
EB: The expected behavior is that obfuscated classes should be less prominent in the 'All Types' dialog.
SR: The steps to reproduce the issue are not provided in the report.
